title: Ex-Texas A&M DE Michael Bennett: I hold JFK's assassination against Dallas-native Matt Stafford
text:
Add another page to the Houston vs. Dallas rivalry.
Michael Bennett attended Alief Taylor High School in the Houston area and went to Texas A&M. After Bennett's Seahawks beat Highland Park native Matt Stafford's Detroit Lions on Monday Night Football, Bennett explained he didn't like Stafford much, simply because he was from Dallas.
"I don't like Matt Stafford much," Bennett told Sports Radio KJR reporter Curtis Crabtree. "He's from Dallas. They killed the President (JFK). ... I hold it against him."
Michael Bennett: "I don't like Matt Stafford much. He's from Dallas. They killed the President (JFK). ... I hold it against him."
